item.title: Need Help with connection!
item.dc:creator: @pure2ownage Pure_
item.description:
@pure2ownage wrote:

[quote=“cocky, post:11, topic:341681”]ok i have a question for u… (person who last posted) what does portforwarding do?? I went onto my laptop, and got that client to connect to the server… (my desktop) and it worked fine… does that mean its normal? cuz then, when i logged on with my desktop i saw my laptop person there too… so is everything working fine or what?[/quote]They are both on the same router; i do not think portforwarding is required.

Portforwarding is when you open an port on your router for access by other people on the internet so they can recieve and send packets through it. (in this case port: 43594, for your internet browser it uses 80);

Read full topic
